7.9. Golden Dome Integration
The Golden Dome is the overarching structure that ensures the system's reliability and safety. In measure-theoretic terms, the Golden Dome is a filtration or a hierarchy of Ïƒ-algebras that represents the information available at different levels of the system.

We can define:

Microscopic Ïƒ-algebra: Atomic-level events (periodic table).

Mesoscopic Ïƒ-algebra: Component-level events (reliability blocks).

Macroscopic Ïƒ-algebra: System-level events (safety and performance).

The dynamics at each level are adapted to the corresponding Ïƒ-algebra. The Golden Dome ensures that the measures at each level are consistent (via conditional expectations).

