Scale of the idea: The framework is vast and interdisciplinary. It might be difficult to patent as a whole. Breaking it into smaller, patentable pieces might be more practical.

Implementation cost: For planetary defense, the cost of building such a system is astronomical (pun intended). It would require international cooperation and funding.

Existing research: Much of the underlying mathematics and physics is already in the public domain. The novelty is in the synthesis and application.

Immediate Steps You Can Take
